===Noun===
{{en-noun}}

# An act or instance of [[deflate|deflating]].
#: ''The loss caused utter '''deflation''' and disappointment among the fans.''
# {{label|en|economics}} A [[decrease]] in the general price level, that is, in the [[nominal]] [[cost]] of [[goods]] and [[services]] as well as [[wages]].
# {{label|en|economics|euphemistic}} An economic contraction.
#* {{quote-news|title=Stans to seek foreign trade|work=Christian Science Monitor|date=March 13, 1969|passage=Beyond that, there is the hope that '''deflation''' of the US economy which the administration has in mind will, overtime; stem the import flood.}}
